FBIS3-55641 "drsov007_o_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 Uzbekistan Further on Arrival LD1001214894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1800 GMT 10 Jan 94 LD1001214894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] President of Kazakhstan Nursultan Nazarbayev arrived today on an official visit to Uzbekistan. The leaders of the two countries signed a package of documents necessary for the creation of a single economic space between Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan. [video shows nazarbayev arriving at airport] [Begin Nazarbayev recording] I think we will open the borders for trade, we will remove the customs barriers, we will remove licensing and quotas; when we are in different monetary systems and national currencies this can only be beneficial. [end recording] The heads of the Central Asian states are to discuss another global problem, the problem of the Aral, which they will visit tomorrow. [video shows President Karimov at airport] [Begin Karimov recording] If today we do not take this initiative then it will be impossible to solve this problem, and its consequences will be felt not only in the lives of people but -- this is most terrible -- on the genetic pool of people, and one cannot look at the future of this region as a whole, and not just this region, without a solution to the problem of the Aral, the Aral problem. [end recording]
